quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,272,"It is not your duty (O Muhammad) to guide them; but Allah guides whom He will; and whatever good you expend it is for yourselves when you spend not save for Allah´s sake. And what you spend of good, it shall be repaid you in full, and you shall not"
  2,273,"(Alms are for) the poor who are straitened in Allah´s way, and cannot travel about in the earth. The ignorant think them to be rich because of their modesty; you will know them by their mark, they do not beg from men with importunity; but what you s"
  2,274,"Those who expend their wealth by night and day, secretly and openly, they shall have their reward with their Lord. No fear shall come on them, nor shall they grieve"
  2,275,"Those who devour usury shall not rise again, save as he rises whom Satan hath paralyzed with a touch; and that is because they say \"trade is only like usury,\" but Allah has made selling (or trade) lawful and usury unlawful; and he to whom the ad"
  2,276,"Allah has cursed usury, but made charity fruitful, for Allah loves not the ungrateful and faithless"
  2,277,"Verily, those who believe, and act righteously, and are steadfast in prayer, and pay the poor due, their reward is with their Lord; there shall no fear come on them, nor shall they grieve"
  2,278,"O you who believe! Observe your duty to Allah, and remit the balance of usury, if you be, in truth, believers"
  2,279,"And if you will not do it, then hearken to the proclamation of war from Allah and His Apostle; but if you repent, your capital is your s. Wrong not, and you shall not be wronged"
  2,280,"And if a debtor be in difficulties, then wait for easier circumstances; but to remit the debt as alms is better for you, if you did but know"
  2,281,"Guard yourselves against the day when you shall return to Allah; then shall each soul be paid what it has earned, and they shall not be wronged"
  2,282,"O you who believe! If you contract a debt for a stated time, then write it down, and let a scribe faithfully record it in writing between you in equity; nor let a scribe refuse to write as Allah taught him, but let him write, and let him who owes dictate"